You sent an attachment.
Want to live a better life? Take a page out of the Stoics and Yogis handbook and IGNORE YOUR IMPULSES. That’s the first step to gaining control over your life and being happy. Remember that it’s not all your fault. Things are designed to be addictive to feed your impulsivity, like your social media, TV, apps, additives in your food, etc. When your brain tells you, “Pick up your phone and doom scroll through social media.” or “C’mon have more ice cream and chips; they taste so good!”, ignore that voice. In a way, you’re ignoring “yourself”. Try this: Every time you feel the need to give into an unhealthy habit, replace that with another action. For example, when you have the urge to scroll mindlessly on Instagram, read a paragraph from a book, journal, or go around your living room for a few minutes. This is more important now than ever because so many things are vying for our attention and triggering different desires, not all of which are good for you. Do you practice ignoring unhealthy impulses in your daily life? Full video ▶️: You Need To Start Ignoring Yourself
